                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>Slightly tapering <objectType>stele</objectType> of white <material>marble</material>, reddish from earth; at top in relief 
                                        a large wreath with ribbons displayed at left and right below it; inside the wreath, a spindle and a roll with a ball of 
                                        wool on it; below the wreath, between the two ribbons, a rosette; on top, a small hole for attachment
                                        (<dimensions>
                                            <width min="0.355" max="0.41">0.355-0.41</width>
                                            <height>1.07</height>
                                            <depth min="0.18" max="0.22">0.18-0.22</depth>
                                        </dimensions>).</p>
                                </support>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> a) just under the rosette; b) below the relief on 12 lines 
                                    (<dimensions><height>0.61</height></dimensions>); the limits of verse-lines are evidenced either through a punct or through a space.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><height min="0.025" max="0.03">0.025-0.03</height>; traces of guidelines, slight serifs, letters packed together, nearly joining; 
                                straight alpha with dropped bar, lower loop of beta larger than the upper one, some (but not all) circular letters smaller, pi with shorter 
                                right stroke, non-slanting sigma, phi with two small loops on both sides of hasta, open omega with large 'feet'.</handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    
